      "content": "okay \"clarification\" sounds a bit flimsy though. if the reporter asks \"but weren't you very specific about the brackets in the June speech?\" and the candidate just says \"it was just a framework,\" it's gonna look like they're dodging. \n\nhonestly, if we get caught in a lie, the sentiment scores will go to zero. can we actually just tell them the truth? like, admit the economy changed and they had to pivot? would that be better for the long-term consistency, or is that just political suicide? give it to me straight.",
